messages.message:
Brian

whats up?

hey Brian!
not much how are you?

Brian
I am peachy
that's good

Brian
soooooo
want to come over and watch a scary movie?
lol...thanks but I'll pass...I can't even sit through a scary preview in a theater, I have to cover my eyes and ears and hum the whole time

Brian
lol
awww
I'm such a wuss

Brian
I really want to finish this movie, but it made me cry last night.

eek
which one are you watching?

Brian
The Tunnel

creepy
does not sound fun
Brian
Can you send me your and your wife's mailing address?  We wanted to invite you guys to our engagement party.  How do you spell her name?

Brian
Iga Cullinan
6934 E Sandra Terrace, Scottsdale, AZ 85254
awesome, very exciting!  congratulations.
Thanks!

Brian
Congratulations again.  Thank you so much for inviting us but Iga and I have to work on Saturday.  But we would like to have lunch with you soon.
Thanks!  Don't work too hard. Lunch sounds lovely.
are you any good with ER diagrams and database schemas?  I have to make one and I am really confused.  I made a sad attempt at one, but I seriously think I did it wrong.

Brian
Yeah, what do you mean by ER diagram?  I can make a schema.
Lol can I email it to you and you can have a good laugh at my lack of computer knowledge?

Brian
ok
What's your email?

Brian
bjcullinan@gmail.com
Can you e-mail me the assignment too?
Ok sent it.

Brian
How much of this did he explain to you?

nothing
Hence why I'm freaking out

Brian
Its like someone explained it to him and then he tries to tell you how to do it.

Brian
His diagram isn't complete

right
we are supposed to create our own databases
and this is our first assignment towards it

Brian
I am so excited to see iron man

me too!  I love iron man
anyways, the assignment is due at midnight, and I'm just trying to see if I can skate by with passing
I just wanted to you see if I'm WAY off the mark with it

Brian
ok, so you need to start with a list of information you want to collect
do you have that?
like, what is the "basic information gathered in the emergency room"?
what I did...the patient last name, first name, DOB, insurance info, etc

Brian
is that all you need?

yeah, it's supposed to be really basic
like probably what you did in 3rd grade

Brian
So you would consider your list in Word, "complete"?

lol for this assignment yes.  But my boxes and arrows I don't think I'm doing right.  They are supposed to show relationship entities.  And he never explained "char" "null" "not null", PK, or why the heck everything has underscores between words

Brian
You can't use spaces in column names in a database
see?  that's useful.  why does no one mention these things

Brian
probably because he doesn't know why.

lol!
so based on what he thinks we are supposed to do, does mine look similar enough to his?
because I was just arbitrarily, writing null, not null, and naming things at random

Brian
not quite, I'll make some edits.
lol just keep it to your 3rd grade computer science glasses

Brian
PK means primary key, it is usually a number that automatically increments by 1 for each row.

*classes
I didn't understand why his diagram had two boxes for address...?

Brian
FK means foreign key, it points from one table to another table's primary key.
that's kinda what I thought, but I don't know if what I was denoting as a foreign key made any sense

Brian
then the lines in the graph go between the tables to graph the foreign keys

I think that's what I did...
anyways, don't kill yourself over it.  I have to turn it in before midnight and I'd be ecstatic just to pass the assignment

Brian
Hmm, this is going to be really incomplete, this is kind of late notice.
well it's really not supposed to be any bigger than his is

Brian
There is regulatory guidance governing this stuff.

lol it's for a make-pretend hospital
not a real one
it's our first schemas we've ever made in our lifetime, so the bar is set pretty low...

Brian
what school do you go to?
Grand Canyon

Brian
This is like exactly what I've been working on for over two years.
I'm glad to see they are teaching it.

Brian
I reformatted the data a bit and e-mailed it back to you.
Technically integers are size 32 or 64
I think I put 8
his, diagram doesn't put a size on integers.
I didn't remove any information I don't believe.
You can view it without track changes using the Review tab.
We can think of some more information to add
You collect medications information right?

Brian
You can view it without track changes using the Review tab.
We can think of some more information to add
You collect medications information right?
yeah, but this should be ok for now

Brian
So, I haven't copied it in to powerpoint
I'll make some more corrections and send you another version ok?

ok, but seriously though, don't waste too much time on it
thanks for looking at it!  I appreciate it

Brian
Yeah, I need to get to bed.
yes get to bed

Brian
almost done
Thanks so much again

Brian
If you can think of any more information hopefully my corrections make sense.
how about insurance phone number?

eh that's ok
this looks awesome!

Brian
I sent the powerpoint corrections.
goodnight

thanks so much!  We owe you drinks sometime
good night!
